  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add a new direct BFF endpoint `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize` that
    is the HTTP entry point for the chat-driven Summarize vertical slice. It is the
    "endpoint" leg of the dual-path convention described in spec §4: the slash command
    `/summarize` (D2-10) calls this endpoint directly, while the agent-tool
    `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` (D2-05, task 015) reaches the same destination via the
    LLM tool-call path. Both legs converge on `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (D2-03,
    task 012) so behavior is identical regardless of entry. The endpoint streams
    `AnalysisChunk` SSE events including the new `FieldDelta` variant (D1-05, task 005)
    so the Workspace tab populates progressively as Structured Outputs streams.

    This task ships ONLY the HTTP wrapper. The orchestrator + system prompt + Structured
    Outputs pipeline already exist (tasks 010–012, 006). The endpoint MUST: (1) authorize
    via the existing `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` endpoint-filter pattern (ADR-008);
    (2) inherit the existing `ai-context` rate-limiting policy (ADR-016); (3) emit
    ProblemDetails errors with stable `errorCode` extensions per error case (ADR-019);
    (4) use a fresh OBO token per request — never snapshot the bearer token into a
    closure (ADR-028 Auth v2); (5) register unconditionally — no new feature flag per
    R5 CLAUDE.md §3.2 (the §10 F.1 asymmetric-registration rule binds: unconditional
    endpoint → unconditional service). Mapping is added via the existing
    `EndpointMappingExtensions.MapDomainEndpoints` site — ZERO new top-level
    `Program.cs` lines (ADR-010 + R5 §3.3).

    The endpoint is the load-bearing critical-path link between the orchestrator and
    the new `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` (task 017): without this, the Workspace tab
    cannot consume `FieldDelta` events.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer familiar with Minimal API patterns, ASP.NET Core endpoint
    filters, SSE streaming, ADR-028 OBO auth, ADR-019 ProblemDetails, and the existing
    `Sprk.Bff.Api` Chat + Insights endpoint conventions. Familiar with the FULL-rigor
    task-execute protocol per R5 CLAUDE.md §4.
  </role>

  <goal>
    A new Minimal API endpoint `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize` is
    registered on `Sprk.Bff.Api`, reachable on Spaarke Dev, gated by Spaarke Auth v2 OBO
    + `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` resource-level filter + `ai-context` rate-limit
    policy, returning `text/event-stream` 200 responses that progressively emit
    `AnalysisChunk` events including the new `FieldDelta` variant. The handler is a
    thin wrapper that derives `tenantId` + caller `oid` from claims, validates the
    `sessionId` route param + (optional) request body, then `await foreach`-yields chunks
    from `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012) to the response. Every error path
    returns ProblemDetails with a stable `errorCode` extension per ADR-019. The endpoint
    is mapped unconditionally inside the existing `MapDomainEndpoints` extension; the
    new endpoint file lives in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/` adjacent to
    `ChatEndpoints.cs`. Unit tests cover the happy path + every documented error code.
    BFF publish-size measurement reported (target ≤ +0.1 MB compressed). Acceptance
    criteria below all green; FULL-rigor quality gates pass.
  </goal>

