  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API only — endpoint is registered via `app.MapPost(...)` inside a `MapXxx(this IEndpointRouteBuilder)` extension method. No Controllers, no MVC.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Resource-level authorization uses an endpoint filter (`AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` extension), NOT middleware. Fires after `RequireAuthorization()` (token validation) and before the handler.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — ZERO new top-level `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`. If any registration is needed (none expected — endpoint only consumes existing `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`), it goes inside `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. Endpoint mapping itself extends `MapDomainEndpoints` in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` — that file is the registration surface, not `Program.cs`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Endpoint lives in BFF (Zone B for AI consumption). Handler injects `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` directly (concrete class per task 012; no interface). Does NOT inject `IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookService`, or other AI-internal types per refined ADR-013 §3.5 facade boundary.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-016">Rate limit — endpoint applies the existing `ai-context` policy via `.RequireRateLimiting("ai-context")` (matches `InsightsAssistantEndpoint` semantics — Assistant aggregate budget shared across AI endpoints). Verify `ai-context` policy exists in `RateLimitingModule.cs` before applying. Do NOT define a new rate-limit policy.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">No new feature flags — endpoint maps unconditionally. Kill-switch coverage inherits from existing `Chat:Enabled` / `Analysis:Enabled` flags via the orchestrator's dependencies (`SprkChatAgentFactory` Null-Object pattern). R5 §3.2 binding.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">ProblemDetails for every error path. Each error case carries a stable `errorCode` string extension (e.g., `sessionId.required`, `sessionId.invalid`, `summarize.no-files`, `summarize.session-not-found`, `summarize.feature-disabled`, `summarize.internal-error`). Pattern mirrors `InsightsAssistantEndpoint.BadRequest()` helper. Never leak document content, prompts, or model output in error detail strings.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Spaarke Auth v2 — endpoint uses fresh OBO token per request. NEVER snapshot the bearer token into a closure. The orchestrator + downstream services receive token via DI-provided `IUserTokenProvider` / `IUserBearerToken` (whichever pattern the orchestrator already uses per task 012); the endpoint MUST NOT capture token into a delegate. Verify by reading orchestrator's signature + downstream Graph/AI client usage.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size verification — measure delta after this task; expect ≤ +0.1 MB compressed (one new endpoint file ~200 LOC). Report absolute size + delta vs baseline in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.1 reuse mandate">MUST reuse `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` (task 012). MUST NOT inline orchestration / playbook-execution / Structured-Outputs logic into the endpoint handler. The handler is the thinnest possible HTTP wrapper.</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §3.3 + ADR-010">ZERO new `services.AddXxx()` lines in `Program.cs`. The endpoint mapping itself is added inside the existing `MapDomainEndpoints(WebApplication app)` method in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` — same file that already calls `app.MapChatEndpoints()` and `app.MapInsightsAssistantEndpoint()`. Add `app.MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint();` (or extend `MapChatEndpoints` if cohesion warrants — discuss in implementation notes).</constraint>
    <constraint source="R5 CLAUDE.md §10 F.1 asymmetric-registration rule">Endpoint mapped unconditionally → underlying service (`SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`) MUST be registered unconditionally in `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` (already done in task 012). Verify before merge. PR will be rejected if asymmetric.</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">BFF additions governance applies — endpoint is a new HTTP surface on `Sprk.Bff.Api`. Pre-merge checklist + Placement Justification section MUST be completed (this task IS BFF placement; explicitly justify vs. shared library or PCF-direct call).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-07">BFF publish-size — current baseline ~45.65 MB compressed; R5 cumulative budget ≤ +1 MB; this task target ≤ +0.1 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-04">Endpoint produces identical output to the slash-command path AND the LLM tool-call path (D2-05). Convergence on `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` is the mechanism.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff/sse-endpoints + bff/auth-filters + bff/problem-details</topic>
