    <patterns>
      <pattern name="SSE-streaming endpoint with auth + rate-limit + ProblemDetails" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Insights/InsightsAssistantEndpoint.cs">
        Canonical reference. Static class with a `MapXxxEndpoint(this IEndpointRouteBuilder)`
        extension; uses `MapGroup` for shared `.RequireAuthorization()` +
        `.RequireRateLimiting("ai-context")` +`.WithTags("...")`; handler is a private
        `static async Task&lt;IResult&gt;` method; validates the request → derives
        tenantId + oid from claims → delegates to a domain service → returns
        `Results.Ok(...)` OR `Results.Problem(...)` with `errorCode` extension. Private
        `BadRequest(string detail, string errorCode)` helper. Mirror this shape exactly.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="SSE streaming handler returning `text/event-stream`" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs (SendMessageAsync, lines 309–611)">
        For SSE: handler signature returns `Task` (not `Task&lt;IResult&gt;`), writes
        `Content-Type: text/event-stream` header, opens `HttpContext.Response.BodyWriter`,
        and `await foreach`-yields chunks from the orchestrator. Pattern in `ChatEndpoints`
        is the closer fit than `InsightsAssistantEndpoint` (single-shot JSON response).
        Combine: use `InsightsAssistantEndpoint`'s validation + ProblemDetails error
        pattern, then for the SSE happy path mirror `ChatEndpoints.SendMessageAsync`'s
        streaming write-loop.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="`AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` extension" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/AiAuthorizationFilter.cs">
        Apply via `.AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` after `MapPost(...)`. Per ADR-008, this
        is the resource-level filter that runs AFTER `RequireAuthorization()` (token
        validation) and BEFORE the handler. Reads document/session IDs from the request
        body or route and verifies access via `IAiAuthorizationService`. Mirrors the
        pattern used by every existing `/api/ai/chat/sessions/*` endpoint.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="ProblemDetails with stable `errorCode` extension" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Insights/InsightsAssistantEndpoint.cs (lines 317–326)">
        ```csharp
        private static IResult BadRequest(string detail, string errorCode)
            =&gt; Results.Problem(
                statusCode: 400, title: "Bad Request", detail: detail,
                type: "https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7231#section-6.5.1",
                extensions: new Dictionary&lt;string, object?&gt; { ["errorCode"] = errorCode });
        ```
        Copy verbatim; vary `errorCode` per error case. For 503 (feature-disabled),
        catch `FeatureDisabledException` and call `ex.AsFeatureDisabled503()` per
        existing extension method.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Endpoint mapping site" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/EndpointMappingExtensions.cs (MapDomainEndpoints)">
        Add `app.MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint();` to `MapDomainEndpoints(WebApplication app)`
        adjacent to the existing `app.MapChatEndpoints();` call. This is the single
        registration surface — Program.cs only calls `app.MapSpaarkeEndpoints()` which
        delegates here. ADR-010 + R5 §3.3 compliance.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Fresh OBO token per request (Auth v2)" location=".claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md">
        Per ADR-028: endpoint MUST NOT capture the bearer token into a closure. Token is
        provided via DI (`IUserTokenProvider` / equivalent) and resolved on each handler
        invocation. The orchestrator (task 012) is responsible for using the DI-provided
        token; the endpoint's only obligation is to NOT snapshot it. Verify the
        orchestrator signature accepts no token parameter (token resolved from DI inside
        the orchestrator/its dependencies).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      D2-04 is the HTTP entry point for the R5 chat-driven Summarize vertical slice. The
      slash command `/summarize` (D2-10, task 019) routes here when
      `ChatSession.UploadedFiles.length &gt; 0`. The Workspace `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`
      (D2-07, task 017) subscribes to the SSE stream this endpoint emits and renders
      `FieldDelta` events progressively (TL;DR first → summary → per-file highlights).
      Without this endpoint, the entire Phase 2 Summarize critical path is blocked.

      The dual-path convention (endpoint + agent-tool both reaching the same
      orchestrator) is the R5 architectural commitment per spec FR-04: identical output
      whether the user types `/summarize` (this endpoint) or asks "summarize the files I
      uploaded" (LLM tool-call via task 015's `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`).
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="010" status="must-be-complete">
        New `sprk_analysisaction` seed "Summarize Document for Chat" deployed to Spaarke
        Dev. The orchestrator (task 012) loads its system prompt from this action row;
        the endpoint indirectly depends on it via the orchestrator.
      </dependency>
      <dependency task="011" status="must-be-complete">
        New `sprk_analysisplaybook` configuration linking the action. Same indirect
        dependency.
      </dependency>
      <dependency task="012" status="must-be-complete">
        `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` concrete class registered in
        `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. This endpoint injects + delegates to it. HARD
        DEPENDENCY — endpoint cannot compile until task 012 lands.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 015 (D2-05) registers the parallel agent-tool path
        (`InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool`). Both this endpoint and the agent-tool converge
        on `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`. Parallel-safe siblings in P2-G3.</item>
      <item>Task 016 (D2-06) adds the additive `workspace.streaming_started`,
        `workspace.field_delta`, `workspace.streaming_complete` PaneEventBus event types
        — frontend-side. Parallel-safe sibling in P2-G3.</item>
      <item>Task 017 (D2-07) builds `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` which consumes the
        SSE stream this endpoint emits. Downstream consumer; gated on 014 + 016.</item>
      <item>Task 019 (D2-10) updates `/summarize` slash command to call this endpoint
        when `ChatSession.UploadedFiles.length &gt; 0`. Downstream consumer.</item>
      <item>`InsightsAssistantEndpoint` (Wave E3) is the closest sibling pattern — same
        auth/rate-limit/ProblemDetails shape, different streaming semantics (Insights is
        single-shot; this endpoint is SSE-streaming).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff summary and request `/compact`.
      Output the mandatory R5 §4.1 rigor declaration:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: BFF code change adding new HTTP endpoint with SSE streaming + Auth v2 OBO + ProblemDetails + critical-path link from orchestrator to Workspace widget.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: Steps 1–10 per this POML with quality gates at Step 9.5.
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress + Verify Dependencies">
      Read `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` and confirm: 014 status is 🔲; dependency 012 status is
      ✅ (orchestrator class exists and is registered in `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`).
      Read `current-task.md` to verify no other R5 task is mid-flight. Read project
      README for status. If 012 is not ✅, STOP and report blocker.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file listed in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract:
      (a) the static class + `MapXxxEndpoint(this IEndpointRouteBuilder)` shape from
      `InsightsAssistantEndpoint.cs`; (b) the SSE streaming write-loop pattern from
      `ChatEndpoints.SendMessageAsync` (line 309 onward); (c) the
      `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` extension signature; (d) the EXACT name of the
      `ai-context` rate-limit policy as registered in `RateLimitingModule.cs` — verify
      string match; (e) `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`'s public signature from task 012
      output (return type — IAsyncEnumerable&lt;AnalysisChunk&gt; expected — and parameter
      list); (f) ADR-028 token-handling rules from `.claude/patterns/auth/spaarke-sso-binding.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Locate Endpoint Mapping Site + Plan File Layout">
      Open `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` and locate `MapDomainEndpoints(WebApplication app)`
      (line 100). Confirm `app.MapChatEndpoints()` at line 141 and
      `app.MapInsightsAssistantEndpoint()` at line 215. Plan: add
      `app.MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint();` adjacent to `MapChatEndpoints` (near line 141).
      Decide endpoint file location:
      `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/SummarizeSessionEndpoint.cs` (matches
      `ChatEndpoints.cs` neighborhood; consistent with the `/api/ai/chat/...` path the
      endpoint owns). Document this decision in task notes.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Author the Endpoint File">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/SummarizeSessionEndpoint.cs` as a
      `public static class SummarizeSessionEndpoint`. Mirror `InsightsAssistantEndpoint`'s
      shape: static `MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint(this IEndpointRouteBuilder app)`
      extension that creates a route group at `/api/ai/chat` with `.RequireAuthorization()`
      + `.RequireRateLimiting("ai-context")` + `.WithTags("AI Chat")`. Inside the group,
      `MapPost("/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize", SummarizeAsync)` with
      `.AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` (ADR-008 resource-level filter). Add `WithName`,
      `WithSummary`, `WithDescription` documenting the dual-path convention (slash
      command + agent-tool converge here). Add `Produces(200, contentType: "text/event-stream")`
      + `ProducesProblem(400|401|403|404|429|503|500)` declarations matching the error
      cases enumerated in Step 5.

      Handler signature: `private static async Task SummarizeAsync(string sessionId,
      [FromBody] SummarizeRequest? request, HttpContext httpContext,
      SessionSummarizeOrchestrator orchestrator, ILogger&lt;SummarizeSessionEndpoint&gt;
      logger, CancellationToken ct)`. Body record (if a body is needed — confirm
      against task 012's orchestrator API): minimal — possibly `fileIds: string[]?`
      and `style: string?` (per spec FR-08 the agent-tool path takes the same shape).
      If orchestrator accepts only `sessionId`, omit the body. Decide based on task 012
      output; document.

      Inside the handler: derive `tenantId` + `oid` from claims (mirror
      `InsightsAssistantEndpoint` lines 162–184). Set SSE response headers
      (`Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`). Open
      `HttpContext.Response.BodyWriter`. `await foreach (var chunk in
      orchestrator.SummarizeAsync(sessionId, tenantId, oid, request, ct))` — write each
      chunk as `data: {json}\n\n` per SSE format mirroring
      `ChatEndpoints.SendMessageAsync`.

      Token handling (ADR-028): do NOT capture token into a closure. The orchestrator
      resolves it via DI inside its own dependencies. Verify by reading task 012's
      output — orchestrator signature should NOT include a token parameter.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Enumerate + Implement ProblemDetails Error Cases">
      Implement these error paths with stable `errorCode` extensions (mirror
      `InsightsAssistantEndpoint.BadRequest()` helper):

      | HTTP | errorCode | When |
      |---|---|---|
      | 400 | `sessionId.required` | Route param empty/missing (defensive — routing rejects normally) |
      | 400 | `sessionId.invalid` | Not a valid GUID / fails session-id format check |
      | 400 | `summarize.no-files` | `ChatSession.UploadedFiles` is empty when this endpoint hit (per spec FR-03 prompt-first path — endpoint refuses; slash command emits interjection instead) |
      | 400 | `summarize.too-many-files` | `UploadedFiles.length &gt; 20` (NFR-02 hard cap — defensive; UI enforces) |
      | 401 | `auth.tid-missing` | `tid` claim absent (auth pipeline misconfig) |
      | 401 | `auth.oid-missing` | `oid` claim absent |
      | 403 | (handled by `AddAiAuthorizationFilter`) | Caller lacks read access to session |
      | 404 | `summarize.session-not-found` | `sessionId` not found in Redis/Cosmos |
      | 429 | (handled by rate limiter) | `ai-context` policy throttled |
      | 503 | `summarize.feature-disabled` | `FeatureDisabledException` propagating from orchestrator (Chat or Analysis flag OFF). Use existing `ex.AsFeatureDisabled503()` extension. |
      | 500 | `summarize.internal-error` | Catch-all; never leak document content or model output in detail string |

      Per ADR-019: every ProblemDetails response includes `correlationId` extension set
      to `httpContext.TraceIdentifier`. Catch order: `OperationCanceledException` →
      rethrow; `FeatureDisabledException` → 503 (FIRST per ADR-032 P3 pattern); other
      domain exceptions → mapped; generic `Exception` → 500 LAST.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Wire Endpoint Mapping into MapDomainEndpoints">
      Add `app.MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint();` to `MapDomainEndpoints` in
      `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` (near line 141 adjacent to `app.MapChatEndpoints();`).
      Add the `using Sprk.Bff.Api.Api.Ai;` import if not already present (likely is).
      Verify ZERO new lines in `Program.cs` — endpoint mapping is invoked transitively
      via `app.MapSpaarkeEndpoints()` → `MapDomainEndpoints` per ADR-010 + R5 §3.3.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Auth v2 Fresh-Token-Per-Request">
      Read the orchestrator code (task 012 output) + its downstream Graph / AI client
      calls. Confirm: (a) no `string accessToken` field captured at construction;
      (b) every per-call token resolution goes through DI-provided
      `IUserTokenProvider` (or equivalent) within scope of the request;
      (c) no `Task.Run(...)` or background-thread continuation that loses the
      `HttpContext`. If any of these are violated, escalate (ADR-028 violation — task
      012 needs follow-up, not 014). Document the verification result in task notes
      (file + line refs to the token-resolution call sites).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Add `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/SummarizeSessionEndpointTests.cs`
      covering: (a) happy path — endpoint reachable, OBO claims parsed, orchestrator
      invoked, SSE chunks written; (b) each ProblemDetails error case from Step 5
      (validate `errorCode` extension value, HTTP status code, no PII leakage in
      detail); (c) `FeatureDisabledException` 503 path; (d) cancellation behavior
      (token cancelled mid-stream); (e) ADR-028 fresh-token contract — assert that the
      orchestrator's token-provider dependency is resolved per-call (mock setup). Mirror
      fixture pattern from existing `InsightsAssistantEndpointTests.cs` /
      `ChatEndpointsTests.cs`. Per R5 §3.7 + CLAUDE.md §10 F.2: inspect fixture config
      FIRST before debugging unexpected DI failures — fixture-config-first protocol.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Build + Test + BFF Publish-Size Verification">
      Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — must succeed with zero new
      warnings. Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` — all new tests pass +
      no existing test regressions. Run `dotnet publish -c Release
      src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`. Measure compressed output
      (`Get-ChildItem deploy/api-publish/ -Recurse | Measure-Object Length -Sum` after
      compression, OR ZIP step depending on existing R5 measurement convention).
      Report: absolute compressed size + delta vs prior baseline (~45.65 MB). Target:
      ≤ +0.1 MB delta. If &gt; +0.5 MB: investigate (one new endpoint file should not
      bloat the publish). If &gt; +1 MB cumulative R5 budget: escalate per R5 §3.6 +
      ADR-029.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` skill against the new endpoint file + the
      `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs` diff + the new test file. Run `adr-check` skill
      verifying: ADR-001 (Minimal API used, not Controllers), ADR-008 (endpoint filter
      not middleware), ADR-010 (zero new `Program.cs` lines — diff `Program.cs`),
      ADR-013 (BFF placement; no AI-internal type injection), ADR-016 (`ai-context`
      policy applied; no new policy defined), ADR-019 (every error returns
      ProblemDetails with stable `errorCode` + `correlationId`), ADR-028 (no token
      snapshot — closure scan), ADR-029 (publish-size measured). Also verify:
      asymmetric-registration rule (R5 CLAUDE.md §10 F.1) — endpoint maps
      unconditionally AND orchestrator is registered unconditionally in
      `AnalysisServicesModule.cs`. Both gates MUST pass. Run static-scan recipe per
      §10 F.1: grep for `if (.*flag.*)` around the new endpoint mapping — must find
      zero matches.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="BFF-Extensions Checklist + Document + Complete">
      Walk through `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` pre-merge checklist (§A–F)
      and tick each item in task notes:
      - § Placement Justification — explicit statement that this endpoint belongs in
        BFF (vs. CRUD code or shared lib). Justification: SSE streaming requires
        long-lived HTTP connection + server-side AI orchestration + OBO auth + rate
        limiting — none of which can be done in a PCF or Code Page. BFF is the only
        viable surface.
      - § AI-PublicContracts facade — N/A (endpoint consumes
        `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` directly, which is the public AI surface
        established by task 012; per refined ADR-013, orchestrators ARE the public
        contract for CRUD code consumption).
      - § Publish-size delta — recorded in Step 9 (≤ +0.1 MB target).
      - § CVE scan — run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` and
        confirm no new HIGH CVEs.
      - § Test obligation — covered by Step 8 unit tests.
      - § Asymmetric-registration — verified in Step 9.5 (unconditional both sides).

      Update task POML status to `complete`. Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 014 🔲 → ✅. Reset
      `current-task.md` to next pending task per CLAUDE.md §7. Record in task notes:
      (a) endpoint file path; (b) error-case enumeration table from Step 5; (c)
      ADR-028 fresh-token verification result with file:line refs; (d) BFF
      publish-size measurement; (e) bff-extensions checklist sign-off. Report task
      completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

