  <examples>
    <example name="InsightsAssistantEndpoint — canonical auth + ProblemDetails shape" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Insights/InsightsAssistantEndpoint.cs">
      Closest pattern for non-SSE concerns: static class layout, `MapXxxEndpoint`
      extension, `MapGroup` with `.RequireAuthorization()` + `.RequireRateLimiting("ai-context")`,
      handler signature with `[FromBody]` + `HttpContext` + DI services + `ILogger` +
      `CancellationToken`, claim extraction for tenantId + oid, ProblemDetails
      `BadRequest(detail, errorCode)` helper, `FeatureDisabledException` catch-FIRST
      ordering, `correlationId = TraceIdentifier` extension. Copy this shape; differ
      only in: (a) SSE streaming response instead of `Results.Ok(JSON)`, and
      (b) `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` resource-level filter (Insights uses a different
      auth layer).
    </example>
    <example name="ChatEndpoints.SendMessageAsync — SSE streaming write-loop" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs (lines 309–611)">
      Reference for the SSE streaming portion of the handler: how to write
      `Content-Type: text/event-stream` headers, how to `await foreach` chunks from a
      domain service and write each as a `data: {json}\n\n` SSE event. Also the
      reference for `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` + `.RequireRateLimiting("ai-stream")`
      usage on a `MapPost` route (note: D2-04 uses `ai-context` per spec, not
      `ai-stream` — confirm policy choice in implementation notes; defer to
      `InsightsAssistantEndpoint` semantics since D2-04 is a tool-equivalent endpoint).
    </example>
    <example name="AddAiAuthorizationFilter extension" location="src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Filters/AiAuthorizationFilter.cs">
      One-line `.AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` application per ADR-008 endpoint-filter
      pattern. Reads document/session IDs from the request (route param OR body) and
      verifies access via `IAiAuthorizationService`. Per R5 §10 — endpoint filters are
      the load-bearing auth surface; do not introduce middleware-level auth.
    </example>
  </examples>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Endpoint `POST /api/ai/chat/sessions/{sessionId}/summarize` is registered on `Sprk.Bff.Api` and reachable on Spaarke Dev (returns 401 without auth header; returns 200 SSE stream with valid OBO token + valid sessionId + populated `ChatSession.UploadedFiles`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Endpoint applies `RequireAuthorization()` (Spaarke Auth v2 token validation) AND `AddAiAuthorizationFilter()` (resource-level read access check) per ADR-008.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Endpoint applies the existing `ai-context` rate-limit policy (per ADR-016); no new rate-limit policy defined; `RateLimitingModule.cs` is unchanged.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">OBO auth works with a fresh token per request — orchestrator + downstream Graph/AI clients resolve token via DI-provided `IUserTokenProvider` (or equivalent); no closure-captured token. Verified via code-scan in Step 7 + unit test in Step 8(e). ADR-028 compliance.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SSE stream emits `AnalysisChunk` events progressively including the new `FieldDelta` variant (D1-05 / task 005). End-to-end test: Workspace tab populates TL;DR field FIRST, then summary, then per-file highlights — incremental rendering, not single big-bang.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Every documented error case returns ProblemDetails with: (a) stable `errorCode` string extension, (b) `correlationId` extension set to `TraceIdentifier`, (c) detail string that NEVER leaks document content / prompts / model output. ADR-019 compliance. Verified by unit tests covering all 11 cases enumerated in Step 5.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Endpoint is mapped UNCONDITIONALLY (no `if (flag)` block around the `app.MapSummarizeSessionEndpoint();` line). `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` is registered UNCONDITIONALLY in `AnalysisServicesModule.cs` (from task 012). Asymmetric-registration rule (R5 CLAUDE.md §10 F.1) verified via static-scan in Step 9.5.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ZERO new top-level lines in `Program.cs` — endpoint mapping added inside existing `MapDomainEndpoints` in `EndpointMappingExtensions.cs`. ADR-010 + R5 §3.3 compliance. Verified by `git diff src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs` showing no changes from this task.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Api/Ai/SummarizeSessionEndpointTests.cs` cover happy path + all 11 error cases from Step 5 + cancellation + ADR-028 fresh-token contract. `dotnet test` is green.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build` clean (no new warnings). BFF publish-size measured + reported in task notes; delta ≤ +0.1 MB compressed vs prior baseline (~45.65 MB); no new HIGH CVEs from `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`. R5 §3.6 + ADR-029.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` pre-merge checklist signed off in task notes, including explicit Placement Justification (why this is in BFF) per R5 CLAUDE.md §10.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">FULL-rigor quality gates pass at Step 9.5: `code-review` + `adr-check` both green. Asymmetric-registration static-scan recipe (R5 §10 F.1) returns zero matches.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
